#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dialogs"
msgstr "Pogovorna okna"

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Palette Manager Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno Upravljalnika palet"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The palette manager allows you to add, remove or swap flosses from your "
"current palette and the selected scheme. You can remove all non used flosses "
"from your current palette and you are able to add new flosses to the scheme. "
"Additionally you can bring up <link linkend=\"CalibrateDialog\">the floss "
"calibration dialog</link> from here."
msgstr ""
"Upravljalnik palet vam omogoča, da dodate, odstranite ali zamenjate nitke iz "
"vaše trenutne palete in izbrane sheme. Iz vaše trenutne palete lahko "
"odstranite vse neuporabljene nitke in v shemo lahko dodate nove nitke. Poleg "
"tega lahko tukaj odprete <link linkend=\"CalibrateDialog\">pogovorno okno za "
"umerjanje zobne nitke</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:14
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can allocate the number of strands of cotton used for each floss, for "
"both stitching and backstitching. This information will be used in "
"calculating the amount of floss required in the final design."
msgstr ""
"Določite lahko število pramenov bombaža, uporabljenih za posamezno nitko, "
"tako za šivanje kot za hrbtno šivanje. Te informacije bodo uporabljene pri "
"izračunu količine nitke, potrebne v končnem dizajnu."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog includes a <guilabel>Pick Color</guilabel> button which allows "
"selection of a color from anywhere on screen. This could be from a "
"background image for example to allow easy selection of matching colors. The "
"cursor will change to a cross with a color swatch indicating the color of "
"the pixel under the cross. After clicking on a pixel, a floss that closely "
"matches the selected color will be selected in the flosses list."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno vključuje gumb <guilabel>Izberi barvo</guilabel>, ki omogoča "
"izbiro barve kjer koli na zaslonu. To je lahko na primer iz slike ozadja, ki "
"omogoča enostavno izbiro ujemajočih se barv. Kazalec se bo spremenil v "
"križec z barvnim vzorcem, ki označuje barvo slikovne pike pod križem. Po "
"kliku na slikovno piko bo na seznamu nitke izbrana nitka, ki se zelo ujema z "
"izbrano barvo."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "Symbol Selector"
msgstr "Izbirnik simbolov"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For each of the flosses you can allocate a symbol. The symbol selector "
"dialog shows all the available symbols. Used symbols are shown grayed out "
"and a tooltip will show <quote>Used</quote> when the symbol is hovered over. "
"For the palette, the symbol library used can also be changed by selecting "
"one from the drop down list. All the flosses will then be allocated a symbol "
"from the new library."
msgstr ""
"Za vsako od nitk lahko dodelite simbol. Pogovorno okno izbirnika simbolov "
"prikazuje vse razpoložljive simbole. Uporabljeni simboli so prikazani "
"zatemnjeni in v opisu orodja bo prikazan <quote>Uporabljeno</quote>, ko "
"premaknete miškin kazalec na simbol. Uporabljeno knjižnico simbolov za "
"paleto lahko spremenite tudi tako, da izberete enega s spustnega seznama. "
"Vsem nitkam bo nato dodeljen simbol iz nove knjižnice."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid "The New Color Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno nove barve"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:45
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog shows the name of the scheme that the new color will be added to. "
"The color requires a name and a description, which can be anything you want, "
"although color name will usually be defined by the floss manufacturer."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno prikazuje ime sheme, ki ji bo dodana nova barva. Barva "
"zahteva ime in opis, ki je lahko poljuben, čeprav ime barve običajno določi "
"proizvajalec nitke."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking on the <guilabel>Color</guilabel> button will show a standard "
"<ulink url=\"help:/fundamentals/colors.html\">&kde; color selection dialog</"
"ulink>. The initial color can be selected and then the parameters can be "
"adjusted to give the correct color."
msgstr ""
"S klikom na gumb <guilabel>Barva</guilabel> se prikaže standardno <ulink url="
"\"help:/fundamentals/colors.html\">&kde; pogovorno okno za izbiro barve</"
"ulink>. Izberete lahko začetno barvo in nato prilagodite parametre, da "
"dobite pravilno barvo."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Once added this new color will be available to be included in your patterns "
"palette via the <guilabel>Palette Manager</guilabel> dialog. It may also be "
"adjusted by using the <link linkend=\"CalibrateDialog\">Floss Calibration "
"dialog</link>."
msgstr ""
"Ko bo ta nova barva dodana, bo na voljo za vključitev v vašo paleto vzorcev "
"prek pogovornega okna <guilabel>Upravljalnik palet</guilabel>. Prilagodite "
"ga lahko tudi z <link linkend=\"CalibrateDialog\">pogovornim oknom za "
"umerjanje nitke</link>."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:61
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Floss Calibration Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za umerjanje nitke"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:65
#, no-c-format
msgid "This dialog has two parts."
msgstr "To pogovorno okno ima dva dela."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the left, a pick list of the schemes that are currently available along "
"with a list of colors that are in that scheme. The color description will be "
"appended with <guilabel>(Calibrated)</guilabel> if the color has been "
"modified by the current invocation of this dialog."
msgstr ""
"Na levi je izbirni seznam shem, ki so trenutno na voljo, skupaj s seznamom "
"barv, ki so v tej shemi. Opis barve bo dodan z <guilabel>(umerjeno)</"
"guilabel>, če je bila barva spremenjena s trenutnim klicem tega pogovornega "
"okna."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the right, is the name and description of the currently selected color, "
"this will be appended with <guilabel>(Modified)</guilabel> if the color has "
"been modified, a preview of the color, and the current RGB values for the "
"color."
msgstr ""
"Na desni strani sta ime in opis trenutno izbrane barve, temu bo dodano "
"<guilabel>(Modified)</guilabel>, če je bila barva spremenjena, predogled "
"barve in trenutne vrednosti RGB za barva."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Also shown is a <guibutton>Reset Color</guibutton> button. This will reset "
"the currently selected color to the value it had when the dialog was first "
"invoked."
msgstr ""
"Prikazan je tudi gumb <guibutton>Ponastavi barvo</guibutton>. To bo "
"ponastavilo trenutno izbrano barvo na vrednost, ki jo je imela ob prvem "
"priklicu pogovornega okna."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pressing the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button will commit all of the changed "
"colors."
msgstr ""
"Če pritisnete gumb <guibutton>V redu</guibutton>, boste potrdili vse "
"spremenjene barve."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:84
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Pressing the <guibutton>Cancel</guibutton> button will restore all the "
"changed colors back to their original values."
msgstr ""
"Če pritisnete gumb <guibutton>Prekliči</guibutton>, boste vse spremenjene "
"barve povrnili na prvotne vrednosti."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:90
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Configuration Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno konfiguracije"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid "This dialog lets you configure a number of elements of KXStitch."
msgstr ""
"To pogovorno okno vam omogoča konfiguracijo številnih elementov KXStitch."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most of the options are self explanatory. The check boxes enable or disable "
"various functions or elements. The pick lists allow selection of the "
"required format of those elements."
msgstr ""
"Večina možnosti je samoumevnih. Potrditvena polja omogočajo ali onemogočajo "
"različne funkcije ali elemente. Izbirni seznami omogočajo izbiro želenega "
"formata teh elementov."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can return to the default set of parameters using the "
"<guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Z gumbom <guibutton>Privzeto</guibutton> se lahko vrnete na privzeti nabor "
"parametrov."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Import Image Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za uvoz slike"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On the left of the dialog there is a preview of the imported image, based on "
"the parameters on the right."
msgstr ""
"Na levi strani pogovornega okna je predogled uvožene slike, ki temelji na "
"parametrih na desni."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The floss scheme for the finished pattern can be selected, by default this "
"is the same as the <guilabel>New Pattern Properties</guilabel> dialog "
"defaults. The maximum colors to be used for the pattern can be enabled and "
"changed as required, by default the imported pattern will have as many "
"colors as are defined in the original image that are converted to floss "
"colors. Checking the <guilabel>Ignore Color</guilabel> box allows you to "
"click the dropper tool to select a color in the image that will be ignored "
"on import. This is useful to remove backgrounds that you don't need "
"converting to stitches. The ignored color will be displayed as a checker "
"board pattern in the preview."
msgstr ""
"Izberete lahko shemo nitke za končni vzorec, ki je privzeto enaka privzetim "
"nastavitvam pogovornega okna <guilabel>Lastnosti novega vzorca</guilabel>. "
"Največje število barv, ki se uporabljajo za vzorec, je mogoče omogočiti in "
"po potrebi spremeniti, privzeto bo imel uvoženi vzorec toliko barv, kot je "
"definiranih na izvirni sliki, ki se pretvorijo v barve nitke. Če potrdite "
"polje <guilabel>Prezri barvo</guilabel>, lahko kliknete orodje za kapljanje, "
"da izberete barvo na sliki, ki bo pri uvozu prezrta. To je uporabno za "
"odstranjevanje ozadij, ki jih ni treba pretvoriti v šive. Prezrta barva bo v "
"predogledu prikazana kot vzorec šahovnice."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The cloth count value defaults to the <guilabel>New Pattern Properties</"
"guilabel> dialog and the scale is set such that the final size is as close "
"to the <guilabel>New Pattern Properties</guilabel> pattern size as possible. "
"These values can be changed as required."
msgstr ""
"Vrednost števila blaga je privzeto nastavljena na pogovorno okno "
"<guilabel>Lastnosti novega vzorca</guilabel> in merilo je nastavljeno tako, "
"da je končna velikost čim bližje velikosti vzorca <guilabel>Lastnosti novega "
"vzorca</guilabel>. Te vrednosti je mogoče po potrebi spremeniti."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Crop image</guilabel> checkbox enables cropping of the preview "
"image. Click and drag across the preview image to select the area required. "
"Guide lines are shown before selecting the starting point to allow more "
"accurate placement. Once an area is selected the preview will be rerendered "
"to show the cropped area. Further cropping can be done if required. Clicking "
"on the reset button, or turning off cropping will revert the preview to the "
"original image."
msgstr ""
"Potrditveno polje <guilabel>Obreži sliko</guilabel> omogoča obrezovanje "
"slike za predogled. Kliknite in povlecite čez predogled slike, da izberete "
"zahtevano območje. Pred izbiro začetne točke so prikazane vodilne črte, ki "
"omogočajo natančnejšo postavitev. Ko je območje izbrano, bo predogled "
"ponovno upodobljen, da prikaže obrezano območje. Po potrebi se lahko izvede "
"nadaljnje obrezovanje. Če kliknete gumb za ponastavitev ali izklopite "
"obrezovanje, se predogled povrne na izvirno sliko."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Use fractionals</guilabel> checkbox will enable the use of "
"fractional stitches in the imported pattern. This effectively doubles the "
"import resolution without affecting the overall size of the pattern."
msgstr ""
"Potrditveno polje <guilabel>Uporabi ulomke</guilabel> bo omogočilo uporabo "
"ulomkov v uvoženem vzorcu. To dejansko podvoji uvozno ločljivost, ne da bi "
"to vplivalo na celotno velikost vzorca."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:137
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking <guibutton>OK</guibutton> will convert the image into a pattern."
msgstr ""
"Če kliknete <guibutton>V redu</guibutton>, boste sliko pretvorili v vzorec."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid "The File Properties Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno Lastnosti datoteke"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pattern size can be defined in units of stitches, centimeters or inches. "
"The width and height values will updated automatically to the equivalent "
"size in the new unit type if the units type is changed."
msgstr ""
"Velikost vzorca je mogoče določiti v enotah šivov, centimetrih ali palcih. "
"Vrednosti širine in višine se samodejno posodobijo na enakovredno velikost v "
"novi vrsti enote, če se vrsta enote spremeni."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The cloth count is defined in units per centimeter or inches and is "
"dependent on the units of size. &ie; if CM is selected for the units then "
"cloth count will be in units per centimeter, similarly for inches. If the "
"<guilabel>Units</guilabel> is changed to <guimenuitem>Stitches</guimenuitem> "
"then the cloth count units will remain as the last CM or inches value."
msgstr ""
"Število blaga je določeno v enotah na centimeter ali palec in je odvisno od "
"enot velikosti. &ie; če je za enote izbrana CM, bo število tkanin v enotah "
"na centimeter, podobno kot za palce. Če <guilabel>Enote</guilabel> "
"spremenite v <guimenuitem>Šivi</guimenuitem>, bodo enote za štetje blaga "
"ostale kot zadnja vrednost v CM ali palcih."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:157
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Title, Author, Copyright and Fabric fields are free text, so you can "
"enter anything you like here. The fabric color can be set by pressing the "
"color button and selecting the required color. This will then be shown in "
"the editor and preview windows."
msgstr ""
"Polja Naslov, Avtor, Avtorska pravica in Tkanina so prosta besedila, tako da "
"lahko sem vnesete karkoli želite. Barvo tkanine lahko nastavite tako, da "
"pritisnete barvni gumb in izberete želeno barvo. To bo nato prikazano v "
"oknih urejevalnika in predogleda."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The floss scheme has a pick list for all the available floss schemes, "
"including any that you have defined yourself."
msgstr ""
"Shema nitke ima izbirni seznam za vse razpoložljive sheme nitke, vključno s "
"tistimi, ki ste jih določili sami."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guilabel>Instructions</guilabel> tab can be used to enter any specific "
"instructions for sewing the pattern."
msgstr ""
"Zavihek <guilabel>Navodila</guilabel> lahko uporabite za vnos posebnih "
"navodil za šivanje vzorca."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Pattern Library Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno knjižnice vzorcev"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The Pattern Library Manager has a hierarchical tree view (more of a forest "
"really) of categories on the left with an icon view of the selected category "
"of patterns on the right. This dialog is non modal and can be left open "
"whilst working on the pattern."
msgstr ""
"Upravljalnik knjižnice vzorcev ima hierarhični drevesni pogled (pravzaprav "
"bolj gozd) kategorij na levi s pogledom ikon izbrane kategorije vzorcev na "
"desni. To pogovorno okno ni modalno in ga lahko pustite odprto med delom na "
"vzorcu."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The simplest way to use the library patterns is to drag and drop them onto "
"the pattern space. Alternatively using the &RMB; on a library pattern will "
"show a context menu with an option to copy it, this can then be pasted into "
"the pattern as many times as required."
msgstr ""
"Najenostavnejši način uporabe vzorcev knjižnice je, da jih povlečete in "
"spustite v prostor vzorca. Alternativno z &RMB; na vzorcu knjižnice prikaže "
"kontekstni meni z možnostjo kopiranja, ki ga lahko nato prilepite v vzorec "
"tolikokrat, kot je potrebno."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Additional items on the context menu are:"
msgstr "Dodatni elementi v kontekstnem meniju so:"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Delete: Delete a library item, for which a confirmation dialog is shown."
msgstr ""
"Izbriši: Izbriše element knjižnice, za kar se prikaže potrditveno pogovorno "
"okno."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:190
#, no-c-format
msgid "Properties: Show the properties dialog for the item."
msgstr "Lastnosti: Prikaže pogovorno okno lastnosti za element."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The properties dialog for each item displays its size and the floss scheme "
"used, the baseline value and the associated keyboard character. The baseline "
"is used to position the character pattern vertically relative to the cursor "
"position when using the Alphabet tool. Positive values move it down, "
"negative values move it up. The associated character is only required for "
"use with the Alphabet tool. After clicking in the associated character text "
"box, the next key press, including modifiers (&Shift;, &Ctrl;, &etc;) is "
"used as the key."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno lastnosti za vsak element prikazuje njegovo velikost in "
"uporabljeno shemo nitke, osnovno vrednost in pripadajoči znak na tipkovnici. "
"Osnovna črta se uporablja za postavitev vzorca znakov navpično glede na "
"položaj kazalke pri uporabi orodja Alphabet. Pozitivne vrednosti ga "
"premaknejo navzdol, negativne pa navzgor. Povezan znak je potreben samo za "
"uporabo z orodjem Alphabet. Po kliku v polje z besedilom povezanega znaka se "
"kot tipka uporabi naslednji pritisk tipke, vključno z modifikatorji "
"(&Shift;, &Ctrl; itd.)."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:203
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create new libraries by clicking the &RMB; on either an existing category, "
"to create a sub category, or on a blank area of the library list, for a new "
"top level category, and select the <guimenuitem>New Category</guimenuitem> "
"option, enter the name and click <guibutton>OK</guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"Ustvarite nove knjižnice s klikom &RMB; bodisi na obstoječi kategoriji, da "
"ustvarite podkategorijo, ali na praznem območju seznama knjižnic za novo "
"kategorijo najvišje ravni in izberite možnost <guimenuitem>Nova kategorija</"
"guimenuitem>, vnesite ime in kliknite <guibutton >V redu</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:207
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Creating a new library pattern by selecting an area in the pattern editor, "
"select copy, then use the &RMB; on an existing category and select paste. If "
"necessary you can use the properties option to add an associated key if you "
"want to use it as a character library."
msgstr ""
"Ustvarjanje novega vzorca knjižnice tako, da izberete območje v urejevalniku "
"vzorcev, izberete kopiraj in nato uporabite &RMB; na obstoječo kategorijo in "
"izberite prilepi. Po potrebi lahko uporabite možnost lastnosti, da dodate "
"povezani ključ, če ga želite uporabiti kot knjižnico znakov."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Library patterns can be dragged and dropped to other libraries in the list "
"to allow you to rearrange them to your needs. Note that there is no checks "
"to ensure that the key codes assigned to library patterns is unique and you "
"should modify any that duplicate an existing one."
msgstr ""
"Vzorce knjižnic lahko povlečete in spustite v druge knjižnice na seznamu, da "
"jih lahko preuredite po svojih potrebah. Upoštevajte, da ni nobenih "
"preverjanj, s katerimi bi zagotovili, da so kode ključev, dodeljene vzorcem "
"knjižnic, edinstvene, zato morate spremeniti vse, ki podvajajo obstoječo."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Text Dialog"
msgstr "Besedilno pogovorno okno"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The text dialog allows you to select a font and size, then enter the text. "
"Clicking <guibutton>OK</guibutton> closes the dialog and returns you to the "
"&kxstitch; window. Positioning the text is the same as pasting any other "
"element. Press the &LMB; on the canvas roughly where you want the text, this "
"will show a preview of the text, position the text exactly where you want "
"it, then release the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Besedilno pogovorno okno vam omogoča, da izberete pisavo in velikost ter "
"nato vnesete besedilo. S klikom na <guibutton>V redu</guibutton> zaprete "
"pogovorno okno in se vrnete v okno &kxstitch; okno. Pozicioniranje besedila "
"je enako kot lepljenje katerega koli drugega elementa. Pritisnite &LMB; na "
"platnu približno tam, kjer želite besedilo, bo to prikazalo predogled "
"besedila, besedilo postavite točno tam, kjer ga želite, nato spustite &LMB;."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extend Pattern Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno za razširitev vzorca"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:233
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is used to extend the pattern in various directions by a number of "
"cells. Enter the number of cells in the spin boxes and press <guibutton>OK</"
"guibutton> to extend the pattern."
msgstr ""
"To se uporablja za razširitev vzorca v različne smeri za več celic. V "
"vrtilna polja vnesite število celic in pritisnite <guibutton>V redu</"
"guibutton>, da razširite vzorec."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Printer Dialog"
msgstr "Pogovorno okno tiskalnika"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:242
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The dialog has a page list on the left showing a thumbnail for each of the "
"pages. The right panel contains the layout editor where the elements can be "
"placed. Each element is customizable using the context menu and can be "
"positioned and sized to suit your requirements."
msgstr ""
"Pogovorno okno ima na levi strani seznam strani, ki prikazuje sličico za "
"vsako od strani. Desna plošča vsebuje urejevalnik postavitve, kamor lahko "
"postavite elemente. Vsak element je mogoče prilagoditi s pomočjo "
"kontekstnega menija in ga je mogoče postaviti v položaj in velikost, da "
"ustreza vašim zahtevam."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select a printer configuration template. Currently a similar one to KDE3 is "
"included."
msgstr ""
"Izberite predlogo konfiguracije tiskalnika. Trenutno je vključen podoben "
"KDE3."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Append a page - This will append a page at the end of the list."
msgstr "Pripni stran – s tem bo stran dodana na konec seznama."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Insert a page - This will insert a page before the one currently selected in "
"the list."
msgstr ""
"Vstavi stran - To bo vstavilo stran pred tisto, ki je trenutno izbrana na "
"seznamu."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Delete a page - This will delete the page currently selected in the list."
msgstr ""
"Izbriši stran – s tem boste izbrisali trenutno izbrano stran na seznamu."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select an element - Used to select elements for editing or resizing."
msgstr ""
"Izberite element – Uporablja se za izbiro elementov za urejanje ali "
"spreminjanje velikosti."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Insert a text element - Used to insert a text element onto the current page."
msgstr ""
"Vstavi besedilni element – Uporablja se za vstavljanje besedilnega elementa "
"na trenutno stran."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Insert a pattern element - Used to insert a pattern element onto the current "
"page."
msgstr ""
"Vstavi element vzorca – Uporablja se za vstavljanje elementa vzorca na "
"trenutno stran."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Insert an image element - Used to insert an image element onto the current "
"page."
msgstr ""
"Vstavi slikovni element – Uporablja se za vstavljanje slikovnega elementa na "
"trenutno stran."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Insert a key element - Used to insert a floss key element onto the current "
"page."
msgstr ""
"Vstavi ključni element – Uporablja se za vstavljanje ključnega elementa "
"nitke na trenutno stran."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When adding elements, select the required element icon, then select the area "
"of the page that the element is to occupy by clicking and dragging with the "
"&LMB; from one corner to another. The properties of the element can be "
"viewed and changed using the context menu accessed by the &RMB;"
msgstr ""
"Ko dodajate elemente, izberite ikono zahtevanega elementa, nato izberite "
"območje strani, ki naj bi ga element zasedel, tako da kliknete in povlečete "
"z &LMB; iz enega kota v drugega. Lastnosti elementa si lahko ogledate in "
"spremenite s kontekstnim menijem, do katerega dostopate z &RMB;"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:264
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The elements can be resized by selecting them using the select "
"tool<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"select-element-icon."
"png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>, this will provide "
"a sizing rectangle around the element. The corners can be dragged around to "
"adjust the size or the whole element can be moved by clicking and dragging "
"using the &LMB;."
msgstr ""
"Velikost elementov lahko spremenite tako, da jih izberete z orodjem za "
"izbiro<inlinemediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref=\"select-element-"
"icon.png\" format=\"PNG\"/></imageobject></inlinemediaobject>, kar bo "
"zagotovilo pravokotnik velikosti okoli elementa. Vogale lahko povlečete "
"naokoli, da prilagodite velikost, ali pa lahko celoten element premaknete s "
"klikom in vlečenjem z &LMB;."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The page has an associated properties dialog which allows setting the page "
"margin and the grid size and visibility. The page margin provides a guide "
"for the placement of objects but does not prevent elements from being "
"positioned outside the defined margin."
msgstr ""
"Stran ima povezano pogovorno okno lastnosti, ki omogoča nastavitev roba "
"strani ter velikosti mreže in vidnosti. Rob strani je vodilo za postavitev "
"predmetov, vendar ne preprečuje, da bi bili elementi postavljeni zunaj "
"definiranega roba."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid "Pattern Element"
msgstr "Element vzorca"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pattern element will show the arrangement of stitches on the grid. The "
"properties dialog can be used to configure how the stitches will be "
"displayed. This allows the element to display as a picture of the pattern or "
"as the working pattern showing the symbols."
msgstr ""
"Element vzorca bo prikazal razporeditev šivov na mreži. Pogovorno okno z "
"lastnostmi lahko uporabite za konfiguracijo, kako bodo prikazani šivi. To "
"omogoča, da se element prikaže kot slika vzorca ali kot delovni vzorec, ki "
"prikazuje simbole."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The pattern element defaults to showing the whole pattern when it is "
"created. Using the properties dialog a selection of the required area can be "
"made in the preview window by clicking and dragging a selection area."
msgstr ""
"Element vzorca privzeto prikazuje celoten vzorec, ko je ustvarjen. Z uporabo "
"pogovornega okna z lastnostmi lahko izberete želeno območje v oknu za "
"predogled, tako da kliknete in povlečete izbirno območje."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:286
#, no-c-format
msgid "Map Element"
msgstr "Element mape"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The map element is used when the pattern spans multiple sheets. It shows the "
"area of the whole pattern that this element represents. It can be enabled in "
"the pattern element properties."
msgstr ""
"Element mape se uporablja, ko vzorec obsega več listov. Prikazuje območje "
"celotnega vzorca, ki ga ta element predstavlja. Omogoči se lahko v "
"lastnostih elementa vzorca."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:295
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text Element"
msgstr "Besedilni element"

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:296
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A text element can be used to add text notes to the pattern or to show "
"titles or comments. The text is configurable with fonts, color and "
"transparency. In addition a border can be displayed."
msgstr ""
"Besedilni element lahko uporabite za dodajanje besedilnih opomb k vzorcu ali "
"za prikaz naslovov ali komentarjev. Besedilo je mogoče konfigurirati s "
"pisavami, barvo in prosojnostjo. Poleg tega je mogoče prikazati obrobo."

#. Tag: para
#: dialogs.docbook:301
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Text elements can also utilize variables which will be converted to "
"properties from the pattern."
msgstr ""
"Besedilni elementi lahko uporabljajo tudi spremenljivke, ki bodo pretvorjene "
"v lastnosti iz vzorca."

#. Tag: title
#: dialogs.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text Variables"
msgstr "Besedilne spremenljivke"

